<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-44-0239 </DOCNO><TEXT>The 1200 MW Trakya power plant in Turkey, which is being built by an internationalconsortium, is the biggest combined-cycle facility with dry cooling inthe world. Phase 1 of the plant, a 600 MW installation, is already operating.The plant expansion is phased to meet steadily growing demand in northwest Turkey. Descriptions of the gas turbosets, heat recovery equipmentand steam turbosets are accompanied by technical data. The dry coolingsystem is necessary to overcome an inadequate cooling water supply atthe site and its operation is outlined. The plant is connected to thenational grid via a 380/154 KV outdoor switchyard with SF/sub 6/ circuitbreakers. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>